column_.text_: So, I hear your husband is a silver artisan?

That's right. Today he's off to Tempeal to buy
materials.

Left here all on my own again. Oh, it gets so 
lonely at times.

Sorry to hear that. And the worst part is, 
Tempeal doesn't even have any nice souvenirs...
The price of tempestone just keeps going up...

Are they really gonna suspend operations at 
the mines? Hm, I could bet on speculation.

You only got one life to live, and a man's 
gotta live it boldly.
Well, someone's in a hurry. Something wrong, dear?

No trip to Folca is complete without having a 
meal with us!

Care for some vegetables, miss? Extra fresh today.
Wouldn't want to miss out!

Well, I am making barley and vegetable soup tonight. 
It's a secret family recipe.
I'm glad we always have Mr. Fix It to rely on.

Yeah, the town wouldn't be what it is without 
him.

Oh, where is he? We agreed to meet by the 
waterwheel...

He makes me wait for him every single time. 
Ugh, I'm going home...

No sign of her. I'm right by the waterwheel, 
just like we planned...
She's not... dumping me... Is she?

How many centuries has it been now since the Empire 
of old drove out the vile Astrals?

Yes, a great many years have passed by in peace... 
and a great many more to come, one hopes.

I'm sick of the country life. Soon enough I'll 
be making it big in the city, just you wait.
Oh, boy, his make-it-bigitis is flaring up again.

Ain't nothing wrong with the simple life, if you 
ask me.
Today could be the day I make my big catch...
Then I'll have something for Mother to eat...

Nothing like a good beer to get you through 
the day!

Have some self-control, would you? We have 
business over in Tempeal after this, remember?

Aw, it'll be the same as always. Not like we're 
gonna run into any trouble on the way or anything!

Hey, move it. I wanna check out that ship that's 
coming in.
Are you gonna sneak onto a ship again?
Papa yelled at you the last time you did that...

Well, no one has to know. I'll be quick. C'mon, 
I can't miss this chance.

Don't be scared of monsters. They won't be 
bothering us.

B-but what if the wyverns in Skywyrm Valley 
attack us?!

Then our Mr. Fix It and the Defense Corps 
will protect us, sweetie.
I'll never find romance here in this backwater...

Maybe it's time I traveled the skies. Oh, I just 
know my soulmate is out there waiting!

Excuse me, I just moved here, and, um... Is it 
true there's a Mr. Fix It who can do anything?

Sure is! He's famous around town. You got any 
problem at all, he'll fix it.

Oh, I wonder if he can help with... 
interpersonal relationships too.

Get this... The girl next door is a total 
believer now.

That can't be good. I mean, the promises of 
salvation are nice and all, but still...

Those people mean trouble. I hope nothing 
happens to her.

Yeah...I can agree with paying respects to 
the primeval gods, but not like that...
I wonder if the primeval gods are real...

We must have greater faith in the primeval gods. 
Only then will salvation come to us...

I don't know... I mean, I know they do a lot 
for us, but...
I agree. That's asking a little too much...

Hey, I heard you used to live in the capital. 
Is that true?

Yeah, I did, but... this town just suits me 
better, you know?

The capital... It must be so wonderful there. 
Life in this town can get a little... dull, 
to say the least.

No problems with the waterwheel! We're all 
counting on you, pal!
Why does no one realize how dangerous they are?

Am I the only one who sees the truth? Then I have
a responsibility to... No, wait, it's too soon...

What are those two up to? Are they going to confess 
their love for each other?
Hm... She can do better though...
B-beautiful day, isn't it?

Yes... Yes it is. Wasn't there something you wanted 
to say to me?

What? Oh, right, um... I hope it stays sunny 
tomorrow... Don't you?
A bountiful harvest of vegetables this year...

Even the folks working in the mines should be able 
to eat their fill.
They sure do eat a lot though...
Nice out today, isn't it...

Seems like just yesterday when there was barely 
half the hustle and bustle in this town.

Well, I'll have plenty of stories to tell when I go 
to join the missus...

And that's how we took the skies back from the 
Astrals. The end.
The Astrals sound really scary...

Haha. You have nothing to worry about. They all 
went back home, beyond the stars.
Ahh... This breeze never gets old...
What! A tornado? In Tempeal?! How! Why!

Stay calm, it'll be okay. Remember, we have Rolan. 
He'll make sure your husband's safe.

An accident in the mines of Tempeal? Looks like 
we're in for another spike in ore prices...

Sheesh, what am I saying? Are the folks working 
the trading post all right?!
Hm? Is something the matter?
You seem to be in quite the rush.
Say that again?! Tempeal was hit by what?!

Anyway, trip's off for now. Let's just see how 
things play out.
They said no kids allowed...
Okay, so let's go play over there!
Was that Rolan whizzing by just now?

I've never seen such a determined face on a man. 
Wouldn't mind seeing it again...

There's a lot of commotion coming from the 
town square. Sounds bad.

Oh, please don't say that. I just moved here. 
I don't need any trouble...
We have drawn the ire of Tempeal's primeval god.

S-so it's true then?! It really was a primeval 
god's doing?

What does this mean? Was it really our lack of 
faith that was the problem?

We must continue to worship it, lest the tragedy 
of Dahli repeat itself...

Something feels off today. Sure hope I'm 
wrong though.

I wonder what all that noise down by the docks 
is about.

I just want to spend the rest of my days in 
peace and quiet.

How is your husband faring? Wasn't he caught up 
in that nasty incident in Tempeal?

My hubby's back to his usual self now. I just 
pray we don't get another scare like that again.
Thank goodness for Rolan and those skyfarers.

Well, I suppose I've got bigger things to worry 
about than ore prices now...

Might be a good idea to invest in the 
reconstruction efforts over at Tempeal.

How are you finding life here in Folca? Settled 
in yet?

Everyone's been so kind to me... But I just want 
to go back to Tempeal...

As chairman of the Folca town council, I promise 
you'll be home in no time.
Times like these call for extra hearty meals!
Stop by and try today's special: pate de campagne!

Will prices go up with all the new folk coming 
in from Tempeal?

Not to worry, miss. Nothing the farmers of Folca 
can't handle.

You know that thing in Tempeal? Seems Rolan went 
and saved the day.

Course he did. We can count on him to do just 
about anything.
He's not here either...
I thought for sure he'd be at this waterwheel...
Huh? That's odd... She's not here either.

Maybe she really is trying to end things with me. 
You'd think she'd at least tell me...
Perhaps I've overstayed my welcome in this world...

I'd hoped to never hear about another tragedy like 
the one in Dahli.
There's talk of Tempeal's primeval god.

Yeah, and it sounds like the Church of Avia 
might be involved too.

Bah. Guess my dreams of heading to the big city 
will have to wait.
I'm going to catch something today too.
Maybe some fish will cheer everybody up.

Today's the day. We're finally back in business 
for Tempeal.

I know they need all the supplies they can get 
for the rebuild, but is it really safe for us to go?

We'll be fine. Word is there's a crew of skyfarers 
working to keep things safe.
There's so many cool ships today!
Come on... Can't we go play somewhere else?

I heard Rolan and the skyfarers beat up all the 
scary monsters!
Wow. That's great news.
They say Rolan came swooping in to save Tempeal.

I wish someone would swoop in and save my 
love life...

Remember the Mr. Fix It I told you about? 
He had a hand in saving Tempeal.

Wow, so he really can fix anything. Maybe 
I'll ask him for help next time.

Looks like the refugee folks have adjusted to 
life here.

My only wish is that they stay healthy during 
their time here.

On a related note, I can't get the rumors of 
Avia's involvement out of my head.

Someone destroyed Tempeal... Was it the 
primeval god?

The primeval gods pass judgment upon us when 
we lose our faith...

We mustn't let the tragedy of Dahli repeat itself. 
Come, let us worship together.
Were Avia's teachings right after all?
Maybe I oughta join Avia too...
Nothing but strange happenings lately...

The commotion at Tempeal's already been dealt with. 
We won't get any more trouble.
Right... I sure hope so.

Looks like the refugees won't be going back to 
Tempeal for a while...

The waterwheel's got even more livelihoods to 
support now. That makes my job all the 
more important.

Witnesses say they saw Avia members running 
around Tempeal.

They're no less dangerous than the Astrals. 
How can people be so blind to the truth?

A girl's heart is easily swayed after something 
scary happens.
Oh, come on! Do something!

Did you hear how Rolan saved the people 
of Tempeal?
Did he now? Well, I'm glad a tragedy was avoided...
Yeah...
Phew, that ought to be plenty of food.
No refugee will go hungry as long as I'm around!
The people of Tempeal have been through so much.

What am I going to tell her? I hope we can go 
back to peace and quiet now.
Mommy, can I go to the church?
Not today, sweetie. Mr. Fix It is busy.

It's remarkable what he did, evacuating the people
of Tempeal with an airship like that.
I can't believe what's happened to Tempeal.

I wonder if there's anything I can do to help. 
Maybe I could hand out food...
It's quiet... I could get used to this.

Come to worship? You're free to join us
anytime.

They say this church has been around for a
long, long time.
I hear there's trouble in Seedhollow...

Is it just me, or does the eastern sky look dark 
and stormy? I hope it's just me...

Okay, calm down. What does Seedhollow need most 
right now?

Food, medicine, blankets... That's right. 
Daily essentials.

We've all heard about the incident in Seedhollow. 
I ask that you remain calm and take rumors with 
a grain of salt.

Rolan and the military are fighting for us, 
so we need to do our part too.
Well, if the chairman says so... I trust him.

I just can't shake this dreadful feeling. 
What's happening to our skies?

No trip to Folca is complete without having a 
meal with us!

Stop by and try today's special: our famous 
drachentrout quiche!

Things look bad in Seedhollow. Will you still 
have enough to sell?

Had a bumper crop last year, so don't worry. 
Storehouse's still full of vegetables that'll 
keep for a while.
Captain! Seedhollow's been attacked by Avia!
D-don't panic! I’m sure Seedhollow's army can handle it!
But if Avia comes here... We won't stand a chance...

You'd think he'd have the decency to be with me 
in these dark times...

I thought I'd catch her for sure this time, but 
still no sign of her...

Damn it. I just wanted to be there to comfort her 
in these dark times.
What has the world come to?
Please, this old man doesn't need any more surprises.

You're not thinking straight! There's no reason 
for you to go!

Seedhollow's still in chaos, last I heard. You 
can still go later, after things have calmed down.

No, I've already made up my mind. If I'm ever 
gonna go to Seedhollow, now's the time.

I'm confident in my muscles, if nothing else. 
I can help with the recovery efforts.

It feels like the incident in Tempeal was just 
yesterday, and now this? What are we to do?!

Don't worry! Tempeal turned out okay in the 
end and so will Seedhollow.

Come, let's get back to work. That's all 
we can do.
What happened at the flower city?

Nothing you need to worry about. The skyfarers 
will save the day.

Everyone's saying something bad's happened. 
I'm scared...

It'll be okay. These skies are full of brave 
people who'll come to the rescue.
I bet Rolan's gone riding off to Seedhollow.
Please, please, please come home safely...
Oh, I hope everybody in Seedhollow's all right...

You came from Seedhollow, didn't you? My thoughts 
are with them...

Just when the Tempeal folks were starting to get 
their lives back to normal...

Maybe we'll get more refugees, from Seedhollow 
this time.

Yeah, Avia talk takes a backseat to the 
humanitarian crisis.

Mama says Seedhollow's in danger... Is another 
primeval god doing it?

I can't believe it... Why would Lady Lilith 
bring harm to people?

Open your eyes. You heard the awful rumors, 
didn't you?

I was this close to being tricked myself! 
So Lilith was just using Avia this whole time!
Seedhollow has its own army. The city'll be fine.

I see, but let us pray for the safety of your 
hometown all the same.

No matter what happens out there, my job will 
always stay the same.

As long as I'm around, this waterwheel 
will never fail!

So they've shown their true colors at last. 
Damn it! I knew it all along!

Next thing you know, not a single corner of 
these skies will be safe. Gah, if only I was 
in a position to stop them...

See, it's not that hard! Just tell her 
everything's gonna be all right.
I guess a little danger gets people in the mood.
It's so sad that so many were hurt in Avia's attack.

I know; it's terrible. But no matter what happens, 
I'm here to protect you.
Huh? What was that?
Erm, sorry! I wasn't trying to... It's not like I...

N-no, no, not at all. But, you know... 
A promise is a promise.
Good barley crop this year, from what I hear.

Still got plenty in storage too. Maybe I could 
spare some to send to Seedhollow.
Nothing good comes of living too long.

Old geezers like me should be the ones kicking 
the bucket first. Young'uns got no business 
hurting each other like that...
Mommy, why does everyone look so scared?

It's nothing you need to be worrying about. 
Go on and play.

This is so sad... How could Seedhollow's 
soldiers let this happen?
I hear the trouble in Seedhollow's been dealt with.

I sure hope so. There's been nothing but 
bad news lately.

First Tempeal, and now Seedhollow, huh? 
We've got a lot of rebuilding to do.

I reckon food will be in high demand for a 
while yet. Maybe I'll sell ore on the side too.
Phew... An official's work never ends.

When will Rolan be back? What if something's 
happened to him?

Oh, he'll be fine. Unplanned trips out of town 
aren't unusual for him.

Nothing like a delicious meal to fuel a hard 
day's work!

Come try today's special: our chateaubrilliant 
roast!
Glad I caught you, miss! Bargain prices today.

Oh, good, those high prices would have been 
the end of me.
Rolan's still not back, huh?

He'd make dealing with all these monsters easier, 
that's for sure.
Come home soon, son. We're all waiting for you.

Gee, look who finally decided to show up. 
Why'd you call me out here?

Um, I've been thinking... We wouldn't keep 
missing each other if we lived together.
So what do you say we get married?
Get married?! Wh-why, yes...
The folks of this world are tougher than I thought.

I guess I'll stick around a little longer and 
see how else they can impress this old man.
Wonder how he's holding up...

Ah, I'm sure he's fine. From what I hear, 
Seedhollow will be back to normal in no time.

We should do our part too. Let's donate all 
the vegetables we can muster.
Everybody's happy again! Hehe.
And it's all thanks to the fish!

Ah, that's the stuff. Cheers to another boring 
and uneventful day.
Yeah. Having a drink, and going to work...

I never realized how precious these dull 
everyday moments were until now.
All the ships are coming back!

Ships are nice, but can we please go somewhere 
else to play?

Guess what, guess what! They said Seedhollow's 
safe again!

See? I told you it would all be okay. Even 
though I was a little worried.
Oh, Rolan... Where in the skies did you go?
I'll be here always, waiting for your return...
I haven't seen Rolan in forever.

Yeah, and with him gone, I hear the town 
council's been bogged down in complaints.
Is there no one else we can turn to for help?

Oh yeah, and the girl next door? She's done 
with Avia.

Well, that's to be expected, given what's 
happened to them.

Still, she always says a prayer to the primeval 
gods before a meal.

Nothing wrong with that, if you ask me. The 
primeval gods do lots for us, and we best 
not forget that.
The primeval gods are alive. Just like us.
We have to care for them too.

Lilith deceived us all, but I still think it's 
important to pay our respects to the primeval gods.

I was blinded by the promise of salvation and 
lost sight of what's truly important.

The primeval gods are our good neighbors. We 
must respect them and work toward our shared futures.
Are you sure about not returning to Seedhollow?

Yeah, I got a letter from family saying everybody's 
all right. That's good enough for me.
Another day of smooth spinning.
The whole town is counting on us, pal.

Peace is back. Or should I say... 
the veneer of peace.

More sinister plans are already in motion, 
I’m sure of it. And this time, I'm going 
to put a stop to them.
Seedhollow is boring again, and so are those two.

I'll never find my own darling if I just watch 
them forever.
A-another beautiful day, isn't it!
Yes, and I hope it stays sunny tomorrow.
Oh, really? Uh, how come?

Isn't it obvious? If it rains, we won't get to 
meet here...
Oh. So you're saying...

Another day, another batch of fresh vegetables. 
I've got the blessings of nature to thank for that.
This'll be enough to feed Tempeal and Seedhollow!

Hey, honey, were you watching? Some out-of-town 
skyfarers saved the day.
It isn't all doom and gloom for this world yet.
The sky's pretty again.
Did Mr. Fix It make it nice and clean for us?
Haha. Yes, sweetie, he sure did.

Wait, the same crew that saved Tempeal also saved 
Seedhollow? Hm...
Peace and quiet can get lonely sometimes...

Rolan's not here... Where'd he wander off 
to this time, I wonder.

This church was built with such great care...
We'd do well to cherish it.

Well someone looks cheerful today. Any good 
news to share?

You have no idea. We're going to be welcoming 
a new member into our family soon.

Congratulations! I can't remember the last 
time I heard such wonderful news!
Where to next? And what to sell?

Feels good being able to trade wherever I 
please again.
Mr. Fix Id, huh? Young man's got fire in his eyes.
Better hurry back, Rolan, or you'll be out of a job.

A delicious meal is the first step to a 
productive day!

Stop by for a bite, and you'll be bursting 
with energy for the rest of the day!
Vegetables, come get your fresh vegetables!

Oh my, love the selection today. Perhaps it's 
time to bring out the old family soup recipe again.
Word is the new Mr. Fix It's pretty trustworthy.

That right? Well, guess we can try asking him 
for help if we ever need it.
Ugh, they're late.

Yeah... I was looking forward to our 
double date today.

It's way past time, and they're nowhere 
to be seen...

Tell me about it. I'm sick of watching this 
wheel spin around.

I got a letter from our buddy. He'll be 
visiting us soon.

What are the odds he brings a bride-to-be 
back with him?
Don't be ridiculous. There's no way... Unless...

I'm gonna catch the biggest fish out of 
everyone at the contest!

Hmm. That boy gets way too wrapped up
in his hobbies...
Still, his serious face is kinda cute...

Another trip to and from Tempeal today. 
Could use some excitement once in a while...

No, I don't need any more happenings, thank you 
very much. There's nothing like an ordinary, 
peaceful day...

When I grow up, I'm going to become a skyfarer 
and protect you from bad stuff!

Ahaha. My hero. I can't wait to see what 
a great skyfarer you'll be.

Id is so charming. My heart races whenever 
I hear his voice...

If Rolan ever comes back, how am I supposed 
to choose?

So, I asked that new Mr. Fix It for advice about 
how to get along with people.
Yeah? How'd it go?

It went well. He listened attentively and gave 
me sincere advice.

Didn't expect that. I swear, I've never seen 
a flicker of emotion cross his face.

Psh, you just don't understand a thoughtful, 
brooding man! He's seen things!

I hear Seedhollow's on its way to recovery. 
Good news at last, eh?

With the threat of Avia gone, I guess Zegagrande 
can finally enjoy peace again.

You know what? Now that Seedhollow's back to 
normal, maybe I should visit after all.

Oooh, would you mind taking me along? I've 
always wanted to go there!

I bet you'd appreciate some Dahli oil 
on you, huh, pal?

Maybe the new Mr. Fix It everyone's been 
talking about could get some for me.

Man, true peace is really quiet. 
A little too quiet...

Almost like it's lulling me into a false 
sense of security! I smell another conspiracy!
Nice weather we're having, aren't we?
Is that really all you have to say?

Spending a calm, peaceful day with you means 
everything to me.
Me too.

People keep saying good things about that 
new Mr. Fix It...

Maybe I'll go say hello with some freshly 
picked greens.

Sorry to keep you waiting, honey, but I don't 
think I can leave this world just yet.

I've still got plenty more stories to hear, and 
I can't wait to tell you all of them when I see you.
Let's pretend to be skyfarers!
But I want to play house!
Heehee... Oh, look at them go...
If only Rolan were here to see this...

I keep hearing about the town's new Mr. Fix It. 
I could use some help myself...

Lately, my husband has been looking out for 
me by helping around the house.

I'm glad he's so willing to help, but I hope 
he's doing okay at work.

Now that we have two Mr. Fix Its around, he has a 
bit more time to spare.

It's thanks to our two Mr. Fix Its that the 
trade route is now safe to travel.

This might be the opportunity of a lifetime! 
Mr. Fix It Buns! Those'll sell for sure!

It's truly a relief knowing Rolan is back 
safe and sound.
He's like family to all of us.
Have you heard the news? Rolan's back!

Indeed, I have. As long as those two are around, 
Folca's future will shine bright.
It appears my dear Rolan has returned.

Ah, but how am I supposed to choose between 
him and Id?

So Rolan is back. It's been a while since I've 
seen him around these parts.

He's back, you say? Well, that's good news, 
if I've ever heard any.

But hmm... Who will I make requests to now? 
Id or Rolan?

Good heavens. Deciding between the two is 
going to be next to impossible.

Water wheel looks to be in good shape today too! 
That's a good omen for this village, I tell you.

Never a day goes by where I'm not thankful for 
our dear friends!

There's something terribly dreary about a day 
when nothing happens.

Perhaps there's a part of me that still yearns 
for new experiences and adventures...

Such nice weather today. I hope the next few 
days are like this too.

It'd be great if it stayed this way until you 
and I grew old. Wouldn't it, my dear?
Word has it that Rolan's back in town.

I should swing by and give him some freshly 
picked vegetables. He's done so much for us, 
after all.

I saw my dear wife in a dream the other day, 
but she just yelled at me to get out.
Mr. Fix It promised that he'd play with me later!
Really? Lucky... I wanna go too!
Well, well... I'm glad to know he's back.

Rumor goes that a band of skyfarers brought back 
Rolan with them. Perhaps it's true...
Nice to see the place has grown so lively.

Rolan was just beaming. Something good happened
to him, no doubt.

Oh, that Rolan. Leaving his stuff here and 
walking off again.
I pray no harm befalls the good people of Tempeal.

It's too bad we had to leave so soon. I was hoping 
to see more of the town.

Haha... Well, once this is over with we can 
go back for some sightseeing.

Folca was such a nice town! Did you get a chance 
to relax too, Katalina?

Please, please, please just let it be a 
case of bad weather...
A primeval god gone mad... I hope no one's hurt.

All right, the wind answers to me now. 
Full speed ahead!
Just hold on... I'll definitely save you.
Lyria...

Lyria must be so scared right now. 
We have to save her.
Yes, and the sooner the better.
We're coming for you, Lyria. You'll see.
Poor Lyria...
When I get my hands on those Aviaeth bastards...

Don't worry, we're in good enough shape to fly. 
We'll catch up to them.

Avia's movements grow more reckless. We must 
use this chance to gain the advantage.
That general was a force to be reckoned with...
Ugh, and we just had the ship all fixed up too.

Mobilizin' a fleet against one ship is overkill. 
Who the hell are these people?

More clouds on the horizon. We might be in 
for a rough ride.

Temporary repairs or not, she's still a bit 
worse for wear...
To go as far as using a mind sealer on Lyria...

Poor girl... I'm sure she resisted until the 
very end.
It's almost as if Lyria has lost her soul...

Those Avia jerks suck! They're not getting away 
with this!

How dare they treat our Lyria like some kinda tool. 
They've got a death wish.
Has Rolan always known what mind sealers are?
Perhaps... I'm overthinking a bit.
Our course is set!

This is just business. You scratch my back, 
I scratch yours.

How vexing... This little detour best not 
take us too long.

This baby's equipped with ether cannons too. 
Do they come standard on all Zegagrande airships?

A slight change of plans, but no change to 
our final goal!

Still can't believe we took down that walking 
fortress. Go us.
There's no time to stall. We must be on our way.
Lyria... Please endure for just a little longer!
Lyria, we're coming to save you no matter what!

The Church's got nowhere left to hide. 
It's time to end this!

Avia's given us quite the runaround. 
Who knows what else they're scheming?
Full speed ahead to Seedhollow!
I must thank you, everyone.

So Lilith was after Seedhollow... I hope 
the people there will be okay.
We need to follow those creeps to Seedhollow now!

They always say "it's hard to see what's right 
under your nose." Either way, we're in for a dustup!

Primal beast Angra Mainyu... This will be 
a difficult struggle to say the least.
Hang in there, Rolan. We're on our way.
Please don't push yourself too hard, Katalina.
Thank you, Lyria. Stay close to me, okay?
It's our turn to do everything we can for Rolan.

Lilith actually wants to destroy the sky itself? 
Well, I won't let her!

I ain't lettin' any of us die. We're all comin' 
back with big smiles.

So that's the Pillar of Vayoi... A tremendous 
primal energy emanates from it.

Man, it's always somethin'... Hang in there, Id. 
We're coming.
Oh, Id...

Id risked his life to return Lyria to us. 
I know what I must do.

It's just not fair... I'll do anything to make 
sure Id comes back with us!

I know the sting of parental betrayal. Hang 
on, Id. We're on our way.

Id, I understand your pain. Just... bear with 
it a little longer.

I don't want anyone to suffer. Let us go and 
save Id!

A change in the Pillar of Vayoi doesn't bode well... 
It's hard not to be on edge.

I swear that guy was about to cry. I'd hate
